{"section": "3.12.1: Using strong induction.", "qid": 0, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  Suppose that the inductive step of a strong induction proof shows that for k \u2265 1, if (S(0) \u2227 S(1) \u2227 .... \u2227 S(k)) is true, then S(k+1) is true.\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   1)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   What statement is equivalent to the inductive hypothesis?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember78\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k, S(j) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember77&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k, S(j) is true.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember80\">\n   <input aria-label=\"For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k+1, S(j) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember79&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k+1, S(j) is true.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember82\">\n   <input aria-label=\"S(j) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember81&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n    S(j) is true.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": ["<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember78\">\n <input aria-label=\"For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k, S(j) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember77&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k, S(j) is true.\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember80\">\n <input aria-label=\"For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k+1, S(j) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember79&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k+1, S(j) is true.\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember82\">\n <input aria-label=\"S(j) is true.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember81&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  S(j) is true.\n </label>\n</div>\n"], "answer": "For k \u2265 1 and any j in the range from 0 through k, S(j) is true.", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n The inductive assumption is that for k \u2265 1, S(0) through S(k) are all true.\n</div>\n"}